column13: N ARE INPUT CONTROL PARAMETERS, A FEW DEPEND DIRECTLY ON CONTROL OUTPUT, REMAINING HAVE INTERDEPENDENCY AND SETPOINTS E.G.I COLUMN. ASSUMED THAT PROCESS WANTS I=1 IDEALLY
M ARE OUTPUT CONTROL PARAMETERS(LABLE= STOP,HOLD,LOWER,RAISE)
THE RELATIONS AMONG CONTROL PARAMETERS ARE SET AT ROW 3, AT ROW 2 IS INITIALIZATIONS
THE CONTROL OUTPUT ACTION DECISIONS ARE SET AT ROW 3 OF M1,M2,M3

PARTICIPANTS FOR EXAMPLE MAY USE 80% ENTRIES FOR TRAINING AND THEN FEED IN REMAINING 20% WITHOUT THE M VALUES, THE MACHINE LEARNING CODE SHOULD PREDICT M VALUES USING THE DECISION TREE IT FORMED USING THE TRAINING DATASET FOR EACH CONTROL OUTPUT, IN SHORT THE CODE LEARNS AT WHICH POINT OPERATOR WILL DO WHAT ACTION
THE SCOPE OF PREDICTED CONTROL OUTPUT FOR THE 20% DATASET VALUES CAN BE TABULATED AND COMPARED WITH THE ACTUAL DATASET VALUES
